<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1796,2040]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1437,152,719]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,1868,1895]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Description:</emphasis>
(female, male unknown): Colour unknown. Integumental papillae more than twice as long as basally wide (
<figureCitation box="[308,388,1904,1931]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1596,1621]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,661,1576]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,661,1576]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 15. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–d. H. amoenoderma, female (MD 151); a. Cx-I+II; b.–d. integument papillae in various views. e.–h. H. poseidon; e. Cx-I+II; f.–h. integument papillae in various views. i.–m. H. sp. inc. nr. lasioderma (MD 061); i. Cx-I+II; k.–m. integument papillae in various views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613332/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
k-m). Lateral eyes lens diameter anterior 55, posterior 40, separation not measurable. Medial margin Cx-I with very inconspicuous projections near setal bases (
<figureCitation box="[895,991,1940,1968]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1596,1621]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,661,1576]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,661,1576]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 15. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–d. H. amoenoderma, female (MD 151); a. Cx-I+II; b.–d. integument papillae in various views. e.–h. H. poseidon; e. Cx-I+II; f.–h. integument papillae in various views. i.–m. H. sp. inc. nr. lasioderma (MD 061); i. Cx-I+II; k.–m. integument papillae in various views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613332/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<date box="[947,991,1940,1968]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="2015-01">15 i</date>
</figureCitation>
), at distal tip a bundle of 9 strong setae. Groups of similar setae in lower numbers at anterior and posterior edge of Cx-II and Cx-III. Posterior margin of Cx- IV with 11 setae in a single row; posterolateral apodeme very short (as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="K. Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[965,1118,2014,2039]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perreptans">
<emphasis box="[965,1118,2014,2039]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">H. perreptans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Swimming setae (anterior/ posterior) II-L-5, 0/0; III-L-4, 0/3; III-L-5, 0/2; IV-L-4, 1/4; IV-L-5, 0/2. Leg claw length (all legs) 33-35; L ratio claw/I-IV-L-5, 11 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[348,362,189,215]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">–</emphasis>
16 %. Leg segments slender (e.g., L/H ratio I-L-5, 4.6; II-L-5, 5.9; III-L-5, 6.1; IV-L-5, 7.2).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Measurements: Idiosoma L/W 1000/875; Cx-I+II, 255/170; Cx-III+IV, 255/230; genital plate 185/60, genital field with 35 pairs of acetabula (4 per transect) and 35 pairs of medial setae. Distal leg segments, given as L/H (ratio): I-L-4, 163/53 (3.1); I-L-5, 218/48 (4.6); II-L-4, 245/55 (4.5); II-L-5, 280/48 (5.9); III-L-4, 230/50 (4.6); III-L-5, 273/45 (6.1); IV-L-4, 325/58 (5.7); IV-L-5, 325/45 (7.2). Mouthparts: Gnathosoma L 190; chelicera L 250, L/H 5.0, basal segment/claw L ratio 4.0; palp total L 383; L/H (ratio) P-1, 40/53 (0.8); P-2, 63/48 (1.3); P-3, 43/43 (1.0); P-4, 165/33 (5.1); P-5, 73/14 (5.3); L ratio P-2/P-4, 0.4, P-4/P-5, 2.3.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,441,467]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks:</emphasis>
This female specimen, found along with a deutonymph, does not fit in the diagnosis of any other species treated here, presenting a mix of characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" box="[759,919,477,503]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lasioderma">
<emphasis box="[759,919,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. lasioderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(integument papillae long and pointed, swimming setae number low, in total only 12 on the legs of each side) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gerecke, 2020" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" box="[922,1093,513,539]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesembrina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[922,1093,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. mesembrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1099,1188,513,539]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1099,1188,513,539]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(leg segments slender and with relatively short claws, acetabula number rather low, see below). Possibly an undescribed species, but more material is necessary for a better definition.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,152,719]" box="[199,732,620,647]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,620,647]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Habitat:</emphasis>
In a pool of a stream at low elevation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,355,656,683]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Distribution:</emphasis>
Only a single record from the southernmost part of 
<collectingCountry box="[944,1081,657,683]" name="Madagascar" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. From the same stream, also 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalonyx">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. megalonyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
